snippet: Tuesday’s special election showed that Alex Sink’s campaign could not outrun the tsunami of advertisements tying her to President Obama’s health care law.
abstract: Florida's special election in 13th Congressional District shows that Democratic Alex Sink could not outrun the tsunami of advertisements by Republican David Jolly tying her to Pres Obama's health care law.

byline.contributor: Jonathan Martin and Jeremy W. Peters contributed reporting from Washington, and Arielle Stevenson from St. Petersburg, Fla.

lead_paragraph: Tuesday’s special election showed that Alex Sink’s campaign could not outrun the tsunami of advertisements tying her to President Obama’s health care law.

headline.main: Health Law Tied to G.O.P. Victory in Florida Race
